<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-06-22T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-06-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0667/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-22T15:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">June 22,
                                        1926—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:15
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>55. Diplomatic body has requested me to join in signing collective note
                            to the Turkish Government requesting that diplomatic and consular
                            officers be exempted from the payment of consumption and other special
                            taxes recently enacted. The note is based essentially on international
                            usage and courtesy. I recommend that I be permitted to join body in
                            making these recommendations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>